The first tribe, where the double nature of the floral envelopes is most evi- dent and complete, is that which comes nearest to the various polypetalous orders, with which Olacinece have been compared. But among these, I can- not admit the affinity to Ant-antiacese. The structure of the seed, where it is so constantly and materially different as in these two orders, becomes one of the most important characters in the classification of Dicotyledons; and it is here accompanied by considerable differences in the fruit, in the ovary, in the aestivation of the corolla, in the texture of the vegetable organs, and other points of habit.
